96e7d1bc-2c79-4ac9-b76f-94b5d4eccaec.11a83738-8268-4d63-b065-13911e39e897.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

96e7d1bc-2c79-4ac9-b76f-94b5d4eccaec.4c403379-65df-4d89-be76-67f58797b5bf.description=
Executes a command from the command line of a remote RAS.

On unix we cannot mandate what type of shell to be used (sh, bash, ksh, csh, etc), so be sure to include the shell in your command
if you need things like file redirection.  Example\:
sh -c "ls -lha /etc > /tmp/myfile"

On Windows, this command will prepend cmd.exe /C or command.exe /C to the command you specify, so there is no need to pass that into this operation.

Inputs\:
    command - the command to execute.
    arguments - any arguments to command.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command.
    path - The path to the commands executable
    cmd_timeout - Timeout in milliseconds before the command is considered failed when returnImmediately is false.
Default value\: 100000 (100 seconds).
    returnImmediately - If true, the operation will execute the command and return immediately.  It will not wait for the command to finish.
Valid values\: true, false.
Default value\: false.

Responses\:
    success - The command executed successfully.
    failure - The command failed to execute.

Results\:
    STDOUT - The standard output of the command.
    STDERR - The standard error output of the command.
96e7d1bc-2c79-4ac9-b76f-94b5d4eccaec.7391df15-acc6-4fd1-a3bd-248818e6640b.description=Releases a lock with an id given by the value of the lockId input. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.

Responses\:
   success - the only response returned.

Results\:
   there are no results.

Notes\:
1) The operation only releases locks acquired by the current run. 
   It cannot release another run's locks.

2) The operation succeeds whether or not there is a lock held 
   by the current run with the supplied id.
96e7d1bc-2c79-4ac9-b76f-94b5d4eccaec.799287ff-6e88-4ed6-9398-b9222f379d8e.description=Attempts to acquire the specified lock, and sleeps until the lock is available. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.
   timeout - The maximum number of seconds this flow will run for.
  seconds - The number of seconds to sleep for between each attempt at acquiring the lock.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock could not be acquired.

Result\:
   Code - 0 if the operation succeeds, 1 otherwise.

Notes\:
1) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

2) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.
